comments: Antetokounmpo (MIL) has two resting hands to Batum's (LAC) back while establishing post position and he releases from the contact to secure the inbound pass.
Batum (LAC) makes contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Holiday (MIL) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the driving shot attempt by George (LAC).
Antetokounmpo (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in George's (LAC) path and absorbs the contact prior to his roll to the basket.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) gathers the ball and takes two steps before releasing his pass.
Leonard (LAC) legally contests the play at the basket by Connaughton (MIL) and any "high-five" contact to Connaughton's hand after the release is deemed incidental.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) has a resting hand to Batum's (LAC) side off ball while he cleanly deflects the entry pass away.
Leonard (LAC) releases from the contact with Antetokounmpo (MIL) on his step back jump shot attempt.
DiVincenzo (MIL) makes contact to Leonard's (LAC) arm that affects his SQBR.
During the inbound, Antetokounmpo (MIL) and Leonard (LAC) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) makes incidental contact with Leonard's (LAC) arm after the release that does not affect his ability to follow through naturally on his jump shot attempt.
As they approach the pick, DiVincenzo (MIL) and Morris Sr. (LAC) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
George (LAC) has a resting hand on Middleton's (MIL) side that he immediately removes as Middleton begins his cut to the perimeter.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) establishes himself in Beverley's (LAC) path as he firms up on his left leg, within his body's natural plane, to absorb the contact that is initiated by Beverley.
Upon receiving the pass, Antetokounmpo (MIL) gathers the ball and takes two steps before his dunk.
Ibaka (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in Antetokounmpo's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs as he slightly turns his shoulder on the defensive switch.
George (LAC) and DiVincenzo (MIL) both make contact to the ball and any contact with each other as they jostle for the rebound is deemed incidental.
George (LAC) commits a take foul on Middleton (MIL).
